HTML
- 2 sections - width 20% and the other one width 80%
- section left: button Clear

JS
- Add the colored div
  - JS file - create a function createColorBox
  - loop 21 times
  - create an element div
  - array of colors 
  - use the color as inline style
      div.style.background = color from the array
  - append the divs to the section from the html
  - add classes
  - addEventListener to each div 
      div.addEventListener("click", retrieveColor)


  - retrieveColor
    - event.target to retrieve the color of the div
    - save the color

- clear button
  - bring the grid back to white

- combination of mouseover, mousedown, mouseup
- boolean to check if the mousedown or mouseover
element.addEventListener("mousedown", func)
element.addEventListener("mouseover", func)


- create the grid
  - JS file - create a function createGrid
  - loop xx times
  - create an element div
  - append the divs to the section from the html
  - add classes
  - event listener click, chenge the color of the div

